It's the answer today,
because we haven't figured out

00:40:22.358 --> 00:40:23.340
how to end bail.

00:40:23.340 --> 00:40:25.940
But the end of bail is
not even radical anymore.

00:40:25.940 --> 00:40:28.210
We did it 20 years ago.

00:40:28.210 --> 00:40:29.620
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:40:29.620 --> 00:40:31.869
AUDIENCE: Thank you so much
for being here and for all

00:40:31.869 --> 00:40:32.390
that you do.

00:40:32.390 --> 00:40:33.830
Two part question.

00:40:33.830 --> 00:40:35.259
Obviously, there's
so much and has

00:40:35.259 --> 00:40:36.800
been for so many
years that makes you

00:40:36.800 --> 00:40:38.770
feel like you're losing hope.

00:40:38.770 --> 00:40:42.120
When you think forward to
2018 and maybe into 2020,

00:40:42.120 --> 00:40:43.954
are there candidates
out there that

00:40:43.954 --> 00:40:45.370
really bring you
hope and you feel

00:40:45.370 --> 00:40:47.720
are inspiring that need
for change that we're all

00:40:47.720 --> 00:40:49.010
looking for?

00:40:49.010 --> 00:40:50.750
And then the second
piece is, since you

00:40:50.750 --> 00:40:53.950
asked this of all your
guests on the pod, what

00:40:53.950 --> 00:40:57.130
is a piece of advice that
has really stuck with you?

00:40:57.130 --> 00:40:59.530
DERAY MCKESSON: That is a
question that I ask on the pod.

00:40:59.530 --> 00:41:02.150
Ocasio-Cortez was more impress--

00:41:02.150 --> 00:41:04.420
I already loved her, and
then I met her and was like,

00:41:04.420 --> 00:41:06.080
I might quit my job
and come work for Oc--

00:41:06.080 --> 00:41:07.020
literally, me and Sam--

00:41:07.020 --> 00:41:09.510
she doesn't have a policy person
